5:
Hey, that place the Guild was talking
about... It was around here, right?
8:
Yes. I sense that there many monsters
about. We must hurry and get the
villagers to safety.
12:
HAAAH! A true knight has arms of
steel! And a heart of gold!
27:
Hah-hah-hah! Coming at me in
numbers, are you?! But I shan't be
cowed! "A true knight stands firm,
even before the very jaws of death!"
31:
Wait. Is he planning to fight all those
ALONE?! And why is he LAUGHING?!
38:
Huh? Oh, right!
Let's do this, Light!
41:
Ah... It seems Lady Fortune has
graced me with allies! I am most
grateful for your aid!
51:
I thank you, young man! I am Gerard,
of the House of Martel. Call me by
my first name, if you wish.
53:
He's, uh... got quite a pair of lungs on him...
I'm Alk, and this is the champion Light.
57:
Alk and Light... What fine names!
Suitable for two gallant—if rather
small—heroes such as yourselves!
61:
...Why challenge all these monsters
on your own? Do you not value
your life?
64:
Why? Because "a true knight is a
bulwark to the people!" It is my duty
to protect!
72:
Well!
...That... is a very good question.
Who WAS I protecting?
79:
I DID meet him last night, after all.
He had his family with him. I, er...
hope they all managed to find shelter.
85:
Sir Knight! D-did you defeat all these
on your own?
88:
Ahh! Look at that! Right on cue!
Are you all right, my good sir?
90:
Yes! But I AM sorry, leaving you and
scarpering on my own like that.
92:
But of course you did! Those monsters
would have been enough to strike fear
into the heart of any peasant! Now,
tell me, are your companions safe?
94:
Oh, yes! The missus and children are
all in one piece!
99: Good! What a relief to hear!
102:
Well, my honorable comrades...
Now that I have fulfilled my duty,
it is time I bid you farewell.
109:
He's fine. Just sleeping. It is a miracle
he even managed to keep awake this
long. He is a most hardy man.
112:
Don't worry. We will look after this
knight.
114:
Oh thank you, good sirs. And when
Sir Knight awakes, give him my thanks
as well. My family and I wouldn't be
alive, if he hadn't been kind enough
to help a stranger in need.
122:
Haha. Just listen to those snores.
Bet he's exhausted.
126:
Yes. Even if we hadn't come, I am
certain he would have fought to his
last breath. Truly, a knight to be
admired.
131:
"A true knight has arms of steel!
And a heart of gold..."
137:
Yeah... I think I'm torn between
admiration... and just finding him
kind of weird.
